sql:
SELECT businesses.name, locations.address
FROM businesses
JOIN locations ON businesses.business_id = locations.business_id;

SELECT AVG(review_count) AS average_reviews_per_business
FROM (
    SELECT business_id, COUNT(*) AS review_count
    FROM reviews
    GROUP BY business_id
);

SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM reviews
WHERE julianday('now') - julianday(review_date) <= 180;

external_knowledge:
Note: 
- The threshold of 50 views is used to gauge the popularity of a business; 
- A business is considered well-performing if its average rating exceeds 4 stars; 
- The term 'up and running' refers to the operational status of a business.
